headline.print_headline: Index Ranks Norway Tops for Well-Being of Elderly
headline.main: Index Ranks Norway Tops for Well-Being of Elderly

lead_paragraph: A global index reflecting economic security, health and other factors — and not deducting for cold winters — ranks Norway and Sweden with the highest level of well-being for older people. Of the 96 nations in the index, Afghanistan ranked last.
